My Bis Nonno (Great Grandfather) Luciano Cacciamani, back in Gubbio, Umbria, Italy in 1919 during the First World War. My Nonno (Grandfather) Federico Cacciamani also fought for the Italian army and was a deminer. He removed land mines around Italy. Once the war was over, he went to South America with my two uncles and had my mother and third Zio (Italian for Uncle) in Venezuela. My mother and the entire family moved to Miami in 1980. I was born in 1985. This is my Cacciamani side of the story! #cacciamani #umbria #italia

Trying 100 Pieces of Chocolate in Belize at the Belizean Chocolate Festival! 🇧🇿 
 
The Belize Chocolate Festival in Punta Gorda It’s just a short flight from Miami and the US! @travelbelize
 
Here are 4 Reasons to Enjoy Belizean Chocolate & Visit the Chocolate Festival:
 
1. Health Benefits: Packed with antioxidants, Belizean chocolate improves heart health, boosts mood, and provides essential minerals like magnesium and iron.
 
2. Immersive Experience: The Belize Chocolate Festival offers firsthand indulgence, educating you on chocolate’s history, production, and health benefits, with a wide range of delectable treats to taste.
 
3. Cultural Richness: Immerse yourself in Belize’s vibrant heritage at the festival, featuring Garifuna music, Mayan rituals, and the customs surrounding chocolate.
 
4. Unique Adventure: Combine your love for chocolate with unforgettable travel. Explore Belize’s stunning landscapes, from turquoise waters to lush rainforests, while indulging in chocolate delights.
 
Click the link in my bio to book your own tripBook Your Own Chocolate Experience Here: https://bit.ly/BTB-davidsbeenhere #TravelBelize #GrabLifeInBelize #GrabLife #BelizeChocolateFestival

I’m David @davidsbeenhere 
Born Sept 4, 1985 in Miami, Florida ☀️ 
I have a diverse heritage, with roots in Italy, Hungary, & Venezuela. 
My maternal grandparents were Italian immigrants. 
My paternal Hungarian grandmother and uncle escaped the Nazis to Austria, and fled to Caracas with my grandfather. 
Spanish is my mother tongue. 
I learned English in school and Italian in college. Now I want to to learn Portuguese and French before my 40th birthday 🫶 
Less than 800 days to go!
